Rustic Turkey Tart
  --Cook's Country

9" round pie dough (store bought or homemade)
1 1/2 c leftover turkey meat, cut into bite-sized pieces
3/4 c crumbled blue cheese
4 firm pears, peeled, cored, and diced
1/4 c pecans, toasted and chopped
1/4 c dried cranberries
1 c sour cream
3 tbsp heavy cream
1 tbsp minced fresh thyme
salt and pepper

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 425F. Gently press pie crust into 9" tart pan and trim ecess dough with knife. Prick bottom of dough all over with tines of fork. Bake until lightly browned, ~15 min; cool on wire rack. Combine turkey, 1/2 c cheese, pears, pecans, cranberries, sour cream, heavy cream, and thyme in large bowl; season with salt and pepper. Transfer mixture to cooled pie crust, then sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake until crust is goldent brown and cheese is melted, ~20 min. Let cool 20 min. Serve warm or at room temp. Tart can be refrigerated for 24 hrs, bring to room temp before serving.
